show.description: In Norse mythology, Odin is often considered the god of the Northern Realm. He is the chief god of the Aesir, associated with wisdom, war, death, magic, and poetry. He is also known as the "All father" and is a prominent figure in Germanic paganism. Watch "God of Northern Realm" Now!
